  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Customer Call List Cleaning Project\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates a data cleaning process for a customer dataset, preparing it for a call campaign. The goal is to standardize formats and filter out customers who should not be contacted."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-1",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 1. Load the Dataset\n",
    "We start by loading the raw data from an Excel file."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Note: Update this path to match your local environment\n",
    "df = pd.read_excel("..\Customer Call List.xlsx\")\n",
    "df"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2. Remove Duplicates\n",
    "Ensuring each customer record is unique."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df = df.drop_duplicates()\n",
    "df"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 3. Clean Last Names\n",
    "Stripping unwanted characters from the `Last_Name` column."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df[\"Last_Name\"] = df[\"Last_Name\"].str.strip(\"/...123_\")\n",
    "df"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 4. Clean and Format Phone Numbers\n",
    "Standardizing phone numbers to a consistent format."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Remove non-numeric characters\n",
    "df[\"Phone_Number\"] = df[\"Phone_Number\"].str.replace(\"[^0-9]\", \"\", regex=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Apply formatting (XXX-XXX-XXX)\n",
    "df[\"Phone_Number\"] = df[\"Phone_Number\"].apply(lambda x: str(x))\n",
    "df[\"Phone_Number\"] = df[\"Phone_Number\"].apply(lambda x: x[0:3] + \"-\" + x[3:6] + \"-\" + x[6:9])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Clean up placeholder strings\n",
    "df[\"Phone_Number\"] = df[\"Phone_Number\"].replace({\"--\": \"\", \"nan--\": \"\"})\n",
    "df"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 5. Decompose Address\n",
    "Splitting the address into Street, State, and Postcode."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df[[\"Street\", \"State\", \"Postcode\"]] = df[\"Address\"].str.split(\",\", expand=True)\n",
    "df"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 6. Standardize Categorical Fields\n",
    "Converting inconsistent labels to a standard 'Yes'/'No' format."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-7",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df[\"Paying Customer\"] = df[\"Paying Customer\"].replace({\"Y\": \"Yes\", \"N\": \"No\", \"N/a\": \"\"})\n",
    "df[\"Do_Not_Contact\"] = df[\"Do_Not_Contact\"].replace({\"Y\": \"Yes\", \"N\": \"No\"})\n",
    "df"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-7",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 7. Final Cleanup and Filtering\n",
    "Removing nulls and applying business logic filters."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-8",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Replace NaN with empty strings\n",
    "df = df.fillna(\"\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Filter out 'Do Not Contact' and missing phone numbers\n",
    "df = df[df[\"Do_Not_Contact\"] != \"Yes\"]\n",
    "df = df[df[\"Phone_Number\"] != \"\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Reset index for the final list\n",
    "df = df.reset_index(drop=True)\n",
    "df"
   ]
  }
 ],
